 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","title":"CI coverage gate workflow + threshold checker","description":"Implement CI workflow that computes coverage metrics and enforces approved thresholds with actionable failure output. Output: gate job plus summary annotations.","design":"Use one threshold checker implementation consumed by local and CI contexts to prevent divergent pass/fail logic.","acceptance_criteria":"- Workflow computes required coverage metrics and validates against policy config without manual interpretation.
- Failure output identifies exact threshold breaches and affected invariant areas.
- Job logs are structured and include links/paths to raw coverage artifacts.","notes":"Include guardrails for transient tooling failures so infrastructure noise is distinguishable from true coverage regression. Unit-shard consistency alignment is validated in bd-mblr.3.1.2 rather than blocking initial coverage-gate workflow implementation.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.393247946Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:50:25.976326114Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:38.215917312Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:37.961549887Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.393247946Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","title":"Invariant-matrix unit coverage drift CI gate","description":"Add CI checker that compares current unit-test evidence against the invariant matrix and fails on critical-path regressions, missing invariant assertions, or mock-only regressions for required unit lanes. Output: deterministic drift report with actionable diffs.","design":"Generate deterministic coverage-drift evidence from invariant matrix artifacts and unit CI outputs, then apply policy thresholds from coverage/no-mock SLO definitions.","acceptance_criteria":"1. CI compares current unit evidence against invariant matrix and fails on critical-path drift, missing assertions, or forbidden mock-only regressions. 2. Drift report is deterministic and includes direct links to failing invariants/tests. 3. Gate integrates with flake policy without masking true regressions.","notes":"This gate is implemented before final flake-policy finalization; flake/quarantine policy (bd-mblr.3.3) then codifies handling based on observed gate behavior.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:32.014075415Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:50:26.080396091Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:45.984727490Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:32.014075415Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:45.161981880Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.6.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:45.708894721Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:45.433463864Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.2","title":"CI E2E Matrix and Artifact Upload Gate","description":"Run required e2e matrix lanes in CI (correctness/recovery/concurrency tiers) and upload structured logs plus repro bundles as artifacts on failure.","design":"Use scenario matrix metadata as single source for lane generation to avoid manual workflow drift.","acceptance_criteria":"- Required E2E matrix lanes (correctness/recovery/concurrency/compat) run in CI with deterministic seeds.
- Failure artifact upload includes logs, seed manifest, scenario IDs, and replay instructions.
- Matrix includes explicit pass/fail policy for required vs optional lanes.","notes":"E2E gate track now combines matrix execution/artifact durability (bd-mblr.3.2.1) with scenario-to-script drift detection (bd-mblr.3.2.2), ensuring required scenarios remain both mapped and executed with reproducible evidence.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:44.931770565Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:58.297984521Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:44.931770565Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:13.580691529Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:13.844209325Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:42:38.530941313Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1349,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CI artifact policy: on failure, upload logs + reduced repro + mismatch diagnostics + environment manifest. Artifacts must be sufficient for offline replay by another engineer/agent.","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:26:13Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","title":"CI E2E matrix workflow + artifact publishing","description":"Implement CI matrix for scenario workloads with deterministic seeds and durable artifact upload policy. Output: reproducible matrix runs with retained diagnostics.","design":"Implement matrix definition as data (manifest) plus renderer, not hand-authored duplicated YAML blocks.","acceptance_criteria":"- CI matrix generation is deterministic and traceable to canonical scenario/seed manifests.
- Artifact publishing is robust: every failure lane produces complete triage bundle with retention policy.
- Workflow output surfaces run_id/scenario_id links so investigators can jump directly to relevant evidence.","notes":"Treat artifact durability as first-class; missing artifacts on failure should itself fail the job. Detailed log-quality conformance is enforced in downstream gates (bd-mblr.3.2.2 and bd-mblr.5.5.3), allowing core matrix/artifact workflow implementation to proceed earlier.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.647642001Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:51:19.230787773Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.647642001Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:38.966556362Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:38.464845668Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","title":"Scenario-to-script coverage drift CI gate","description":"Add CI checker that validates canonical scenario catalog coverage against script/test traceability manifests and fails when required scenarios are unmapped or unexecuted in required lanes. Output: machine-readable gap diff and human summary.","design":"Compare canonical scenario catalog against script/test traceability and executed lane manifests to detect both mapping drift and execution drift.","acceptance_criteria":"1. CI validates canonical scenario catalog coverage against script/test manifests and required execution lanes. 2. Fails when required scenarios are unmapped or not executed with required artifacts/logging. 3. Produces machine-readable gap diff and concise operator summary for remediation.","notes":"This gate consumes consolidated script-suite readiness via bd-mblr.4.5.3 and core matrix behavior via bd-mblr.3.2.1. It is intentionally decoupled from final script-log conformance gate (bd-mblr.5.5.3) so scenario-drift enforcement can be implemented earlier, with combined assurance enforced later at CI policy level.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:32.043386147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:32:41.030328633Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:31:20.998504842Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:47.633253091Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:46.539768818Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:47.363805786Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1356,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Restored parent-child link to bd-mblr.3.2 so CI drift gate remains grouped under CI E2E gate family and appears in parent rollups/plans.","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:31:28Z"}]}
+{"id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","title":"CI E2E matrix workflow + artifact publishing","description":"Implement CI matrix for scenario workloads with deterministic seeds and durable artifact upload policy. Output: reproducible matrix runs with retained diagnostics.","design":"Implement matrix definition as data (manifest) plus renderer, not hand-authored duplicated YAML blocks.","acceptance_criteria":"- CI matrix generation is deterministic and traceable to canonical scenario/seed manifests.
- Artifact publishing is robust: every failure lane produces complete triage bundle with retention policy.
- Workflow output surfaces run_id/scenario_id links so investigators can jump directly to relevant evidence.","notes":"CI matrix workflow consumes the canonical orchestrator manifest (bd-mblr.4.5.2) plus artifact schema so lane definition remains deterministic and drift-resistant. Treat artifact durability as first-class; missing artifacts on failure should itself fail the job.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.647642001Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:50.775115118Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.647642001Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:38.966556362Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:38.464845668Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:45.626266368Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","title":"Scenario-to-script coverage drift CI gate","description":"Add CI checker that validates canonical scenario catalog coverage against script/test traceability manifests and fails when required scenarios are unmapped or unexecuted in required lanes. Output: machine-readable gap diff and human summary.","design":"Compare canonical scenario catalog against script/test traceability and executed lane manifests to detect both mapping drift and execution drift.","acceptance_criteria":"1. CI validates canonical scenario catalog coverage against script/test manifests and required execution lanes. 2. Fails when required scenarios are unmapped or not executed with required artifacts/logging. 3. Produces machine-readable gap diff and concise operator summary for remediation.","notes":"This gate consumes consolidated script-suite readiness via bd-mblr.4.5.3 and core matrix behavior via bd-mblr.3.2.1. It is intentionally decoupled from final script-log conformance gate (bd-mblr.5.5.3) so scenario-drift enforcement can be implemented earlier, with combined assurance enforced later at CI policy level.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:32.043386147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:25.248978013Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:31:20.998504842Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:47.633253091Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:46.539768818Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:44:47.363805786Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:16.407627433Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1356,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Restored parent-child link to bd-mblr.3.2 so CI drift gate remains grouped under CI E2E gate family and appears in parent rollups/plans.","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:31:28Z"},{"id":1359,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Restored direct dependency on bd-mblr.5.5.3 so scenario coverage drift gate only activates after script logging conformance checks are in place (prevents false confidence from scenario coverage without diagnostics quality).","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:33:25Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.3","title":"Flake Budget, Retry Policy, and Quarantine Workflow","description":"Define explicit flake budget for unit/e2e/coverage jobs, safe retry strategy, quarantine process, and escalation path so CI gates stay reliable without masking real regressions. Output: policy + automation hooks + incident workflow.","design":"Model flake handling as policy config + enforcement hooks so decisions are reviewable and versioned.","acceptance_criteria":"- Flake budget is numerically defined per gate class with clear escalation thresholds.
- Retry policy distinguishes infrastructure/transient failures from correctness failures and prevents masking regressions.
- Quarantine workflow includes owner assignment, expiry, and mandatory follow-up issue linkage.","notes":"Flake policy is derived from observed behavior of implemented CI gates (bd-mblr.3.1.1, bd-mblr.3.1.2, bd-mblr.3.2.1, bd-mblr.3.2.2, bd-mblr.3.4.1). Policy intentionally follows gate implementation; redundant parent blockers are removed where transitive prerequisites already enforce order.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:47.984613898Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:30:17.729313310Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:47.984613898Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:10:09.366539335Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:50:16.844808293Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:10:09.445968630Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:50:16.940537966Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T01:30:11.979952042Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.4","title":"No-Mock Critical-Path Enforcement Gate","description":"Add CI assertion that each designated critical path has at least one non-mock, real-backend test lane and that this requirement is reviewed when new critical paths are introduced.","design":"Drive validation from invariant coverage matrix instead of ad-hoc hardcoded test name lists.","acceptance_criteria":"- Gate validates each critical invariant/path has at least one non-mock test lane in required CI execution.
- Gate blocks changes introducing new critical paths without corresponding non-mock evidence.
- Gate report maps each invariant/path to its proving tests for auditability.","notes":"This enforces the project’s real-behavior test philosophy and prevents regression to mock-only confidence.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:51.056490827Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:04:59.236464660Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:12.814095669Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:13.068455733Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:13.323155864Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:51.056490827Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","title":"No-mock critical-path CI gate rule","description":"Enforce CI rule that critical-path verification must be satisfied by real-backend tests, not mock-only suites. Output: auditable rule implementation and failure messaging.","design":"Implement rule over structured invariant/test mapping generated from bd-mblr.1.3.2 artifacts.","acceptance_criteria":"- CI rule evaluates non-mock critical-path evidence with deterministic pass/fail semantics.
- Rule emits precise failure diagnostics (missing path, expected proving tests, observed evidence).
- Rule supports controlled, expiring exceptions with explicit owner metadata.","notes":"No-mock CI rule depends on completed unit/integration drift gates and real-backend evidence tasks. Redundant direct blockers (already guaranteed transitively) are removed to reduce fan-in without weakening assurance.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.898484590Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:30:17.658561551Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.1.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:39.730009324Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:39.221983210Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:39.478218481Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:04:45.090294703Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:45:37.867486581Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:45:38.139547138Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:08.898484590Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
