 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","title":"Failure artifact bundle schema and collector","description":"Define artifact bundle schema (logs, seed, workload, DB snapshots/diffs, environment metadata) and implement collector integration. Output: one-bundle-per-failure triage package.","design":"Treat bundle writer as reusable library component with schema validation and versioning support.","acceptance_criteria":"- Artifact schema includes logs, seed manifest, workload inputs, expected/actual diffs, and environment metadata.
- Collector integration writes one deterministic bundle per failure with scenario_id/run_id indexing.
- Collector is validated by tests that intentionally trigger failures and inspect bundle completeness.","notes":"Schema should align with unified logging fields; alignment is validated by downstream log-quality gates (bd-mblr.5.4.1) so artifact-bundle implementation can proceed in parallel with schema refinement.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:55.648991504Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:43:36.363171610Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:35.127327962Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:35.383497319Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:35.638929346Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:37:55.648991504Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.4.5","title":"Complete E2E script-suite coverage and execution manifest","description":"Create an authoritative map and runner strategy for every e2e integration script so the suite is complete, deterministic, and auditable. Scope: inventory all e2e/*.sh and equivalent integration entrypoints, map each to canonical scenario IDs, identify blind spots, and define one reproducible execution manifest covering required environment, ordering, and expected artifacts.","design":"Treat script-suite coverage as a data product: maintain machine-readable manifest + traceability matrix consumed by CI and triage tooling.","acceptance_criteria":"- Authoritative inventory includes every E2E script entrypoint with deterministic invocation contract and scenario coverage mapping.
- Execution manifest defines canonical ordering/sharding rules, required environment, and artifact expectations.
- Any uncovered scenario is explicitly flagged with rationale and linked remediation task.","notes":"This track complements scenario implementation by guaranteeing script-level executability and auditability of the full E2E surface.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:28:54.704231383Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:43:17.834582533Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T00:28:54.704231383Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
